<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1632.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Russell</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-04T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1915—4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Before considering increase of indebtedness to convention fund and
                            proposed loan or any non-constructive measures which would afford but
                            temporary relief, the Department will await a report of your efforts to
                            obtain revised convention contemplated in instruction No. 139 of
                            September 17, which was drawn solely with a view to assist the Dominican
                            Government in devising some means to provide permanent financial relief,
                            to improve present unsatisfactory land <pb facs="0444" n="328" xml:id="pg_328"/> laws, and to preserve public order so as to secure
                            Dominicans in the peaceful development of the vast natural resources of
                            their country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>